{{ Song arrangement, with an added verse and pre-chorus, retitled as "Immanuel Is His Name" (2026) }}

O rejoice, all you peoples of the Earth!
Rejoice, for the Lord is with us,
And God is among us,
And Immanuel is His name.

For unto us He was given,
And for our sake He was slain;
To buy for us a pardon
He suffered our pain.

O rejoice, all you peoples of the Earth!
Rejoice, for the Lord is with us,
And God is among us,
And Immanuel is His name.

Truly God in His essence,
He came down and took on flesh,
Through suff'ring, learnt obedience,
Became the death of our death!

But our Lord, He is risen,
And the Name He is given:
It's above every name.
His glory we shall proclaim!

O rejoice, all you peoples of the Earth!
Rejoice, for the Lord is with us,
And God is among us,
And Jesus is His name.

Jesus is His name.

